# Branch and pull request workflow

These repositories use a mirror setup. Work only through feature branches and pull requests.

## Repositories

| Repo | Default branch | Origin (work here) | Upstream (auto-sync on merge) |
|------|----------------|--------------------|------------------------------|
| webrtc-live | `main` | Calatayud-Digital-Solutions/webrtc-live | AdiCampan/webrtc-live |
| EbenEzerLive-MOBILE | `master` | Calatayud-Digital-Solutions/EbenEzerLive-MOBILE | AdiCampan/EbenEzerLive-MOBILE |
| evidenta-biserica-firebase | `main` | Calatayud-Digital-Solutions/evidenta-biserica-firebase | AdiCampan/evidenta-biserica--firebase- |
| church-organizer | `master` | Calatayud-Digital-Solutions/church-organizer | AdiCampan/church-organizer |

## Mandatory workflow

1. Never commit or push directly to the default branch (`main` or `master`) on `origin`.
2. Before changes, update the default branch: `git fetch origin` and branch from `origin/<default>`.
3. Create a descriptive branch: `feat/...`, `fix/...`, or `chore/...`.
4. Commit on the feature branch and push to `origin`: `git push -u origin <branch>`.
5. Open a PR to the default branch on `origin` (CodeRabbit reviews here).
6. Do not push to `upstream` manually unless the user explicitly asks.
7. After merge to the default branch, GitHub Actions syncs to AdiCampan automatically.

## Pull request creation

Use `gh pr create` against `origin`, targeting the repo default branch.

Example for `webrtc-live`:

```bash
git checkout -b feat/my-change origin/main
# ... changes ...
git push -u origin feat/my-change
gh pr create --base main --head feat/my-change --title "feat: my change" --body "## Summary\n- ..."
```

For repos with `master`, replace `main` with `master`.

## Agent constraints

- Do not run `git push origin main` or `git push origin master`.
- Do not merge to the default branch locally; use the PR on GitHub.
- Do not create commits on the user request unless they are on a feature branch.
- If work started on the default branch, create a feature branch before committing.
